["train_val2019", "test2019"]: return "/".join(parts[1:]) return file_path def extract_tar_files(): train_val_path = "input/train_val2019.tar.gz" test_path = "input/test2019.tar.gz" if not os.path.exists("working/train_val2019"): print("Extracting train_val2019...") with tarfile.open(train_val_path, "r:*") as tar: tar.extractall(path="working") if not os.path.exists("working/test2019"): extract_tar_files() # Load training and validation data with open("input/train2019.json") as f: train_data = json.load(f) categories = train_data["categories"] category_id_to_label = {cat["id"]: idx pd.DataFrame( [ { "id": ann["image_id"], "file_name": image_id_to_file[ann["image_id"]], "label": category_id_to_label[ann["category_id"]], } for ann in data["annotations"] ] ) train_df = create_df(train_data) # Create validation split from training data val_df = train_df.sample(frac=0.2, random_state=42) train_df = train_df.drop(val_df.index) # Data transforms train_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.RandomResizedCrop(380), transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(), transforms.ColorJitter(brightness=0.2, contrast=0.2, saturation=0.2), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) val_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(456), transforms.CenterCrop(380), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) class INaturalistDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, root, transform=None): self.df = df self.root = root self.transform = transform def __len__(self): return len(self.df) def __getitem__(self, idx): row = self.df.iloc[idx] img_path = os.path.join(self.root, row["file_name"]) img = Image.open(img_path).convert("RGB") return self.transform(img), row["label"] if self.transform else img train_ds = INaturalistDataset(train_df, train_root, train_transform) val_ds = INaturalistDataset(val_df, train_root, val_transform) batch_size = 64 train_loader = DataLoader( train_ds, batch_size=batch_size, shuffle=True, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True ) val_loader = DataLoader(val_ds, batch_size=batch_size, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True) model = models.efficientnet_b3(pretrained=True) model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(model.classifier[1].in_features, num_classes) device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = model.to(device) criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss() optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=3e-4, weight_decay=0.01) scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.OneCycleLR( optimizer, max_lr=3e-4, steps_per_epoch=len(train_loader), epochs=10 ) best_val_acc = 0 for epoch in range(10): model.train() for x, y in tqdm(train_loader, desc=f"Epoch {epoch+1}"): x, y = x.to(device), Accuracy: {val_acc:.4f}") if val_acc > best_val_acc: best_val_acc = val_acc torch.save(model.state_dict(), "working/best_model.pth") print(f"Best Validation Accuracy: {best_val_acc:.4f}") class
